mutant: m041_identity_swallowed
target: internal/ingest/live/events.go
failure-mode: |
  convertIdentity silently swallows every #identity event (returns
  nil, nil — the same shape as the legitimate #info no-op arm), so
  identity events vanish from the archive while the cursor advances
  past them. This models the info-style-no-op regression class: a
  refactor of ConvertEvent's dispatch that folds #identity into the
  "informational, nothing to archive" branch would ship exactly this
  bug, permanently and silently losing an entire event kind. Before
  #202 the simulator never emitted #identity, so this exact edit was
  invisible to every oracle tier (the m013/m014 green-by-vacancy
  lesson).
expected-detection: |
  default tier: the world's default TrafficMix emits #identity frames
  and the harness injects deterministic ones (bootstrap handle-absent,
  steady handle-change + malformed-DID). With conversion swallowed the
  bootstrap-live consumer archives nothing for the injected identity
  frame, the exact-count bootstrap ack never reaches its target, and
  the after-bootstrap barrier times out; if traffic pacing lets the run
  proceed, assertIdentityArchived and the exact-multiset event-log
  compares (expected side decodes #identity from firehose history) fail
  on the missing rows. The live-package unit tests for convertIdentity
  and the corpus tier's real-frame decode regression also fail.
expected-tier: default
tiers: default

